main event: Unidentified object observed moving in the sky over Houston, Texas on multiple occasions in June 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at high speeds, making abrupt stops and changes in direction, and exhibiting behavior different from known aircraft.
The object was observed over the course of several days, with multiple sightings recorded at different times and locations around the city.
The object was described as a bright, star-like object that could suddenly accelerate to very high speeds without any visible means of propulsion.
The object was observed descending towards the ground and then suddenly shooting back up to a higher altitude.
The object's movements were described as smooth, controlled, and precision-like, unlike any known aircraft at the time.
